<doc id="417501" wikidata="Q104961898" url="?curid=417501" title="Bob McCartney">
<text>Robert McCartney was a Scottish footballer who played as a defender. He began and ended his senior career with Leith Athletic, spending his prime years at Heart of Midlothian where he won the Scottish Cup in 1896 and the Scottish Football League championship in 1896‚Äì97, playing in all but one of the 18 fixtures; he also claimed two winner&#x27;s medals each from the minor Rosebery Charity Cup (to add to one from his first spell at Leith) and East of Scotland Shield.

McCartney was selected once for the Scottish League XI in January 1898.

