<doc id="417607" wikidata="Q89674" url="?curid=417607" title="Friedrich August Berthold Nitzsch">
<text>Friedrich August Berthold Nitzsch (19 February 1832, in Bonn ‚Äì 21 December 1898, in Kiel) was a German theologian.

The son of Karl Immanuel Nitzsch, he became professor ordinarius of theology at Gie√üen in 1868 and at Kiel in 1872. He was the author of &quot;Das System des Boethius&quot; (&quot;The system of Boethius&quot;; 1860) and &quot;Grundriss der christlichen Dogmengeschichte&quot;, t. I, &quot;Die patristische Periode&quot; (&quot;Outline on the Christian history of dogma, part 1: The patrician era&quot;; 1870), amongst other texts.

